p.q:
That, for the purposes of any Act of the present Session to provide for the granting of proprietary lights to persons who breed or discover plait varieties, it is expedient to authorise—


(1) the payment out of money provided by Parliament of—


(a) the remuneration and allowances of the members of any tribunal or other body established under the said Act and of any officers or servants appointed under the said Act;

(b) the expenses of any body established or officer appointed under the said Act, including any fees paid by any such body or officer to any other person in respect of that person in maintaining any reference collection of plant material;

(c) any expenses incurred by any Minister in the execution of the said Act;

(d) any increase attributable to the said Act in the sums payable under any other enactment out of money so provided;


(2) any payments into the Exchequer.
